Deflect (Defense)									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary							DESC:A Jedi learns to deflect projectiles with his lightsaber, thereby providing a dodge bonus to Defense against such attacks. You must be carrying an activated lightsaber to use this special ability. Deflecting an attack is a reaction that costs the Jedi a move action in his next round. The Jedi must indicate that he using deflect (defense) when an opponent declares an attack against his but before any attack rolls are made. When used in this fashion, the Jedi gains the dodge bonus against him but before any attack rolls are made. When used in this fashion, the Jedi gains the dodge bonus against all ranged attacks directed at him in the round. Each time the Jedi gains deflect (defense), it provides a +1 dodge bonus to AC when he uses his lightsaber to block ranged attacks. So, at 1st level dodge bonus to AC is +1, and increases by 1every two levels thereafter.
Deflect (Attack)									CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary							DESC:A Jedi learns to deflect certain attacks with his lightsaber at 3rd level, redirecting the attack toward a target within one range increment of the Jedi's position. You must be carrying an activated lightsaber to use this special ability. Deflecting and redirecting an attack is a reaction that costs the Jedi a move action in his next round. The Jedi must indicate that he using deflect (attack) when an opponent declares an attack against him but before any attack rolls are made. Deflect (defense) and deflect (attack) can be used together in the same round (though the Jedi can decide not to use the defense if he wants a better chance at redirecting the incoming attack). The Jedi can deflect and redirect a number of attacks equal to his class level. The redirected attack mist miss the Jedi by 5 or less: any attack that hits the Jedi or misses by 6 or more points can't be redirected. If the Jedi can redirect the attack, the Jedi immediately rolls an attack using his lightsaber attack bonus and applying a -4 penalty. If this roll is high enough to hit the target, the redirected attack deals damage to the target. Each time the Jedi gains deflect (attack), the penalty associated with redirected attack lessened by 1 every two levels.
Deflect (Extend Defense and Attack)						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary							DESC:At 4th, a Jedi learns to extend his defensive and offensive deflection skills to others within 5 ft. of the Jedi position. You must be carrying an activated lightsaber to use this special ability. Now the Jedi can provide a dodge bonus to anyone within 5 ft. of his position, and he can deflect and redirect ranged attacks made against anyone with 5 ft. of his position. All rules associated with deflect (defense) and deflect (attack) apply; the only difference is that now the Jedi can extend this ability to help those nearby.
Increase Lightsaber Damage							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary							DESC:As a Jedi gains levels, the amount of he can deal with his lightsaber increases. Each time the Jedi gains lightsaber damage, the weapon's damage increases by +1d8.
Block											CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary							DESC:This is a modified version of deflect attack that allows the Jedi to deflect a ranged attack without use of a lightsaber. The Jedi must have some form of protective gear or an item that can withstand the ranged attack. The dodge bonus provided by deflect (defense) is used when a Jedi blocks a ranged attack with out a lightsaber. Block doesn't allow a Jedi to redirect the attack or to extend the defense beyond the Jedi's position, and all other rules concerning deflect (defense) apply.
